Question: How do I collect multiple maximum values from a List: :How to get max from an ArrayList that has more than one max? For example, if an ArrrayList contains max = 20 stored at index 2, 3 and 6, how do you get all that indicies?
Please using this api: SortedMap.firstKey.
Answer:


*

*<<<api>>>: SortedMap.firstKey

*<<<code>>>:



SortedMap<Integer, Integer> map = new TreeMap<>();
map.put(1, 10);
map.put(2, 20);
map.put(3, 20);
map.put(4, 20);
map.put(5, 10);
map.put(6, 20);
map.put(7, 10);
map.put(8, 10);
map.put(9, 20);
map.put(10, 10);

int max = map.lastKey();

List<Integer> maxIndex = new ArrayList<>();

for (Map.Entry<Integer, Integer> entry : map.entrySet()) {
    if (entry.getValue() == max) {
        maxIndex.add(entry.getKey());
    }
}

System.out.println(maxIndex);



*

*<<<explanation>>>:



The SortedMap.firstKey() method returns the first key in the map.
  The SortedMap.lastKey() method returns the last key in the map.
